<TITLE> Sajib Wazed wants mother free 'right now' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Sheikh Hasina's son Sajib Wazed Joy Wednesday demanded freedom of his mother. "Let my mother be released right now. She was arrested in a false case," Sajib living in the US told bdnews24.com by phone, hours after the High Court cancelled an extortion case against his mother. He said the High Court upheld the constitution and law of the country through the verdict. "It would be inhuman to keep my mother in jail noweven for a moment," he said. The High Court scrapped the extortion case filed by businessman Azam J Chowdhury against the Awami league president and ruled illegal its trial under emergency powers rules. bdnews
